The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 China backs Pak peace plans

 Beijing, Feb. 21 (PTI): China today welcomed Pakistans efforts to promote peace in South Asia as the two countries opposed terrorism, proliferation of weapons of mass destruction and their means of delivery. 

 The joint statement issued here after bilateral meetings between Pakistani President Pervez Musharraf and the Chinese leadership said the two countries discussed international and regional developments.

 China vowed to respect Pakistans independence and territorial integrity and supported Islamabads efforts to promote peace in South Asia.

 Pakistan pledged its committment to the one-China policy and recognised that the government of the Peoples Republic of China is the sole legal government representing the whole of China. 




